          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "P-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   Protons on tritium-titanium target used",
                " for neutrons from 1.06 to 2.88 MeV."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                "   Deuterons on a 3 cm long gas target with",
                " a 2.2 micro-m thick havar entremce foil, filled",
                " to a pressure of 1.6 kg/cm2 with deuterium gas,",
                " was used from 4.31 to 6.83 MeV neutron energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Parallel type ionization chamber, con-",
                " taining 90% Argon and 10 per cent C-H4."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SOLST"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Silicon surface barrier detectors were",
                " used for alpha counting to make quantitative ana-",
                " lyses of the fission samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The fission samples were electropolated on Pt",
                " plates and sintered into oxide to fix them on",
                " the plates. The americium and uranium samples",
                " were placed back-to-back in the fission chamber.",
                ".The composition of the samples were",
                "  sample   thickness  isotope   atom-     number of",
                "          micro-g/cm2          percent   atoms X e+17",
                "   U-235     90.3      U-234    0.03         --",
                "                       U-235   99.91    11.34+/-0.15",
                "                       U-236    0.04         --",
                "                       U-238    0.02         --",
                "   Am-243    17.8     Pu-239    0.02         --",
                "                      Pu-240    0.03       0.001",
                "                      Am-241    0.02         --",
                "                      Am-243   99.63    2.157+/-0.018",
                "                      cm-244    0.30       0.006"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".Corrections were applied for background due to spon-",
                " taneous fission and fissions by room-scattered",
                " neutrons.",
                ".Corrections were also applied for fission events",
                " occuring under the alpha pulses, impurities in the",
                " samples and neutron spectra, neutron scattering,",
                " and absorption in the samples."
              ]
            }
          ],
